Cornell's Adult University participants return to the Ithaca campus Friday afternoon following a four-day cycling tour of the Finger Lakes region.
The CAU Bike Warriors program, led by Cornell Outdoor Education staff, began Monday with a daytime tour of the Ithaca area; the group of 7 participants and 3 instructors then departed Tuesday morning on the extended tour, staying at state parks while visiting lakes, parks, gorges and the occasional winery and cycling an estimated 170 miles total during the four-day trip.
@cornellcau @cornelloutdoors

Arts Quad sculpture (detail): “Urchin,” built from 360 plastic deck chairs by architecture assistant professor Caroline O’Donnell (created by her design firm CODA and student assistants).
It is part of the Cornell Council for the Arts’ 2016 Biennial, “Abject/Object Empathies,” which includes 12 new projects by artists working to “suggest how the objects, buildings, interfaces and images we construct are shaped by the intentional or implicit emotional, interdependent relationship to others.”
